00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:09.930
WHO WOULD HAVE THOUGHT
THAT BABIES HAVE

00:02:09.930 --> 00:02:12.160
SIX DIFFERENT TYPES OF CRIES?

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.930
AND IT'S YOUR CHALLENGE
AS A PARENT OR CAREGIVER

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:17.600
TO FIGURE OUT WHICH
CRY MEANS WHAT.

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:21.600
BABIES WILL CRY WHEN THEY ARE
HUNGRY, TIRED, WET OR DIRTY,

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:24.060
HAVE PAIN,
DISCOMFORT, OR TENSION

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:26.200
AND EVEN WHEN THEY ARE BORED.

00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:28.300
DON'T WORRY, YOU'LL ONLY
NEED TO HEAR EACH CRY

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:30.560
A FEW TIMES BEFORE
YOU'LL SOON BE ABLE TO

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:32.400
DISTINGUISH AMONG THEM.

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:35.200
AND REST ASSURED, BABIES
WILL ALSO LET YOU KNOW

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:39.530
WHEN THEY ARE HAPPY AND
THAT IS A WONDERFUL SOUND.

00:02:39.530 --> 00:02:41.500
WELL, NOW WITH HER BEING
JUST FOUR WEEKS,

00:02:41.500 --> 00:02:45.030
SHE HAS HER CRY THAT
I CAN KIND OF DISTINGUISH.

00:02:45.030 --> 00:02:47.360
I DISTINGUISHED
IT THE FIRST WEEK

00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:49.300
'CAUSE SHE CRIES REAL HARD AND

00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:52.700
IT'S AROUND THAT THREE HOUR
TIME WITH HER FEEDING.

00:02:52.700 --> 00:02:55.530
SO, SHE GETS REAL
RED AND SHE'S READY.

00:02:55.530 --> 00:02:57.730
IF I MAKE HER WAIT A
COUPLE OF MINUTES

00:02:57.730 --> 00:02:59.100
TO WARM UP THE BOTTLE.

00:02:59.100 --> 00:03:00.760
SO, WE KIND OF
DISTINGUISHED THAT

00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:02.130
AFTER A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

00:03:02.130 --> 00:03:06.200
HE HAS DIFFERENT CRIES FOR WHEN
HE NEEDS CHANGING AND FEEDING.

00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:09.660
WHENEVER HE CRIES,
IF HE NEEDS FEEDING,

00:03:09.660 --> 00:03:11.960
WE GIVE HIM A BOTTLE AND
IF THAT DOESN'T WORK,

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:13.900
I KNOW HE NEEDS CHANGING.

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:15.860
EVENTUALLY,
AT ABOUT SIX MONTHS,

00:03:15.860 --> 00:03:18.030
CRYING WILL BECOME
LESS FREQUENT,

00:03:18.030 --> 00:03:20.860
BUT UNTIL THEN, RESPONDING
TO A NEWBORN'S CRIES

00:03:20.860 --> 00:03:24.930
WILL ENHANCE DEVELOPMENT BY
CREATING A SECURE BABY.

00:03:24.930 --> 00:03:27.900
SUDDEN OR LOUD NOISES MAY
ALSO CAUSE A NEWBORN

00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:31.700
TO CRY AS THEY ARE STARTLED
EASILY AT THIS AGE.

00:03:31.700 --> 00:03:34.600
HOWEVER THIS SAME STARTLE
REFLEX IS AN IMPORTANT

00:03:34.600 --> 00:03:37.030
DEVELOPMENTAL MILESTONE
AND WILL BE APPARENT

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:39.930
FOR UP TO SIX MONTHS OF LIFE.

00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:43.660
ANOTHER REFLEX APPARENT FROM
BIRTH IS THE ROOTING REFLEX.

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:45.800
A NEWBORN WHOSE CHEEK IS
GENTLY STROKED

00:03:45.800 --> 00:03:48.060
WILL TURN IN THE
DIRECTION OF THE STIMULUS,

00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:50.800
MOUTH OPEN READY TO SUCKLE.

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:53.560
NEWBORNS WILL ALSO USE
THEIR STEPPING REFLEX

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:56.200
IF HELD UPRIGHT ON A FLAT
SURFACE AND THEY WILL

00:03:56.200 --> 00:03:59.460
ACTUALLY APPEAR
TO BE WALKING.

00:03:59.460 --> 00:04:03.030
THE PALMER GRASP AND
PLANTAR GRASP ARE FUN

00:04:03.030 --> 00:04:05.360
TO PRACTICE WITH
NEWBORNS AS WELL.

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:07.700
THE PALMER REFLEX WILL
CAUSE A BABY TO GRASP

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:10.600
YOUR FINGER IF YOU PRESS
IT AGAINST HER PALM,

00:04:10.600 --> 00:04:13.160
WHEREAS THE PLANTAR
REFLEX CAUSES TOE CURLING

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:15.230
WHEN YOU RUN YOUR FINGER
ALONG THE BOTTOM

00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:18.030
OF A BABY'S FOOT.

00:04:18.030 --> 00:04:21.230
HEY, CAMERON.

00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:23.460
ALTHOUGH THEY ARE UNABLE
TO TALK JUST YET,

00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:26.160
BABIES ARE LEARNING TO
COMMUNICATE FROM DAY ONE,

00:04:26.160 --> 00:04:28.530
SO IT'S A GOOD IDEA TO
SMILE AND TALK TO YOUR BABY

00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:31.400
AT ALL TIMES, WHILE
CHANGING DIAPERS, BATHING,

00:04:31.400 --> 00:04:33.360
AND FEEDING.

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:35.960
FROM BIRTH, NEWBORNS ARE
ABLE TO FOCUS ON OBJECTS

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:40.860
WITHIN 8 TO 15 INCHES, SO
THEY CAN SEE YOU AND HEAR YOU.

00:04:40.860 --> 00:04:42.760
THIS COMMUNICATION
ENHANCES A BABY'S

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:46.400
DEVELOPMENT AND
SOCIALIZATION SKILLS.

00:04:46.400 --> 00:04:48.630
NEWBORNS WILL ALSO
QUICKLY LEARN TO FOLLOW

00:04:48.630 --> 00:04:51.060
A HUMAN FACE WITH THEIR
EYES AND RESPOND TO

00:04:51.060 --> 00:04:53.600
A VOICE WITH THEIR
HEAD AND EYES.

00:04:53.600 --> 00:04:56.360
SO ALTHOUGH, THEY WON'T BE
TALKING FOR MANY MORE MONTHS,

00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:58.600
THEY'VE ALREADY BEGUN
TO COMMUNICATE WITH YOU

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:00.830
ON A SPECIAL LEVEL.

00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:03.660
SHE'S BECOMING MORE AWARE
OF MY VOICE EVERY DAY.

00:05:03.660 --> 00:05:06.600
THE FIRST TEN DAYS THEY
REALLY DON'T UNDERSTAND

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:09.660
YOUR VOICE.

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.400
THEY START TO GET
TO KNOW YOUR VOICE.

00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:14.400
AND SHE'S LOOKING
AT ME A LOT MORE.

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:16.330
I'VE JUST NOTICED
THE LAST WEEK.

00:05:16.330 --> 00:05:17.260
SHE'S LIKE, "OH!"

00:05:17.260 --> 00:05:19.100
YOU KNOW, AND STUDYING MY FACE.

00:05:19.100 --> 00:05:21.660
HE'S STARTING TO
HOLD HIS HEAD UP.

00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:23.130
HE COOS A LITTLE.

00:05:23.130 --> 00:05:24.930
HE SMILES, YOU
KNOW, IN HIS SLEEP.

00:05:24.930 --> 00:05:26.630
HE SMILES AT US.

00:05:26.630 --> 00:05:29.330
IF YOUR BABY SEEMS NOT TO
BE REACHING ONE OR MORE

00:05:29.330 --> 00:05:31.830
OF THE MILESTONES DISCUSSED
THROUGHOUT THIS PROGRAM,

00:05:31.830 --> 00:05:33.730
ON A CONSISTENT BASIS,

00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:36.060
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO CHECK WITH YOUR DOCTOR.

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.200
HOWEVER, KEEP IN MIND
THAT CHILDREN DEVELOP

00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:41.100
AT DIFFERENT RATES SO THE
DIFFERENCES YOU MAY NOTICE

00:05:41.100 --> 00:06:11.430
COULD BE QUITE NORMAL.

